# Workspace Rules - planning-poker-dev

## Responsibility

`planning-poker-dev` owns local orchestration, Docker Compose, Caddy, deploy scripts, CI notify workflows and canonical documentation for the microservices stack. It must not contain application business logic.

## Workspace Map

| Cursor folder | Repo path | Responsibility |
|---|---|---|
| `dev` | `planning-poker-dev` | Compose, deploy, CI, docs |
| `web` | `planning-poker-web` | React/Vite SPA |
| `voting-service` | `planning-poker-voting-service` | CMS, sessions, RBAC, scope, retro, AI |
| `jira-service` | `planning-poker-jira-service` | Jira/GitLab adapter |
| not listed | `planning-poker-python-lib` | Shared pure Python library |

Legacy `telegram_pb` is not used in production and must not be edited without explicit user request.

## Canonical Docs

- Start here: `docs/TECHNICAL.md`.
- Service boundaries: `docs/architecture/SERVICES.md`.
- Auth/RBAC: `docs/architecture/AUTH.md`.
- Data/storage: `docs/architecture/DATA.md`.
- API contracts: `docs/contracts/**`.
- Developer practices: `docs/development/GUIDE.md`.
- List pagination: `docs/development/LISTS.md`.
- Shared lib pin/release: `docs/architecture/PYTHON-LIB.md`.
- Production deploy: `infra/deploy/PRODUCTION.md`.

Update docs in this repo whenever behavior, API, env/config, deploy workflow, service boundary or shared-lib process changes.

## Where To Change Infra

| Change | Path |
|---|---|
| Compose stack | `docker-compose.yml`, `docker-compose.prod.yml` |
| Caddy/reverse proxy | `infra/caddy/**` |
| Production deploy scripts | `infra/deploy/**` |
| CI notify workflows | `.github/workflows/ci-notify-*.yml` |
| Stack validation | `Makefile`, `.github/workflows/ci.yml` |
| Reference k8s manifests | `infra/k8s/**` |

## Verification

- Docs-only changes: validate links/paths and final diff.
- Compose changes: run `docker compose config`.
- CI/deploy/script changes: run the narrow script validation available locally and then `make check` when practical.
- Cross-service contract changes: run `make test` from this repo.
- Broad stack changes: run `make check` from this repo.

## Deploy

Deploy only on explicit user request. Use the production runbook in `infra/deploy/PRODUCTION.md`; do not infer deploy from merge, push or PR creation.
